==English==

===Etymology===
Shortened form of “How do you do?” and also a way of hi

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aʊdi|-aʊdi]]

===Interjection===
'''howdy'''

# (''US, generally rural'') An informal greeting.
#: ''Howdy folks, and welcome to our ninth annual chili cookoff!''

===Noun===
'''howdy'''
# (''British, Noth and Scotland, archaic'') A greeting. Short for how-d'ye-do (how-do-you-do).

===Noun===
'''howdy''' or '''howdie'''
# (''Scottish'') A wife, a midwife.

